rComments: Her content for Biostatistics is actually easy. But she explains in only 1 way. Unlike Prof Punzalan who explains in atleast 3 ways so a majority of people can understand. Really enjoyed this course. Be sure to really focus on the assignment as it can make or break your grade, dont leave it till the last minute. Midterm & exam were fair.

Nice, chill, brings snacks to class, however, didn't like her as a professor. Lectures were unorganized. Probably most caring prof at Uoft. Use to bring food and stuff in in-class tutorials. Easy going with marking. She is amazing and the course (EEB375) is really soft and interesting (even if u r not "eeb-person")

Great & easy going prof. At times it is hard to understand how she teaches certain concepts but a quick google search can help you understand what she is trying to explain in an instant. Great prof, tests and quizzes are based heavily on lectures. Need a bit of extra review on your own to understand some concepts. Really willinging to help students, especially outside of classroom
Very unorganised professor. Can't convey material properly and the test was not reflective of her lecture slides. She is also very unhelpful during office hours.

Midterms/exams were fair. If you read all the assigned material, do all the assignments, and took good lecture notes you should have no problem getting an A in the class. She doesn't explain some concepts too well but still a fine prof overall.
Cannot convey the material clearly, very unorganized and rarely knows the answers to questions asked. I do not recommend this prof!!!

This professor is much clearer than the full-year professors. Even though it is a summer course the class never felt rushed. There is a lot of material to learn but it's definitely possible to get an A if you do all of your work and go to class. She was really great, down to earth.

she may be a nice person, though she cannot teach. she never knows any answers when asked, and her exams consist of graphs you may have only looked at once. STUDY GRAPHS!  she is also very unorganized
